Cumberland University offers more than 100 different degree programs to choose from, meaning you can rise and pursue the career you want with a degree from CU. Before your academic journey can begin, you first have to apply and be accepted. Don’t feel overwhelmed. We’re here to answer all of your questions to be sure you feel confident and ready for the next step. Whether you’re an incoming freshman, transfer student or graduate student, we have enrollment specialists who guide you through the entire admissions process. Check out the guide below to learn how to become a Phoenix in just eight easy steps.
"I instantly felt a sense of camraderie because of the diversity, sociability, and fellowship on campus."

The Cumberland University invites interested students and parents to visit our campus for Preview Day! The day will include conversations about college planning, academic programs, scholarships and financial aid, and most importantly, information about why you should become part of the CU family. You'll meet Cumberland students who will discuss several aspects of college life. You'll meet faculty members who will talk about our programs of study. You'll tour our academic, housing and athletics complexes. You'll enjoy a day on our beautiful campus, eat with us and learn all about CU.

Choosing a college is a major decision that will impact the rest of a student’s life. So, how do you find out if Cumberland University is the right choice for you? Visit our campus! Campus visits will allow prospective junior and senior high school students, as well as prospective transfer students, to experience Cumberland University firsthand. We believe that college is an experience that will change your life. Come see why CU will change your future!

Visiting the Cumberland campus is the best way to see for yourself what CU is all about. On a campus visit you will have the opportunity to tour the campus, meet current students, tour a residence hall, and learn about scholarship opportunities at CU. For your convenience, campus visits are offered almost every weekday during scheduled appointment times. We recommend that you reserve a time below for your campus visit to ensure the best experience possible.

Please fill out the form below to schedule your campus visit. (We request that students make campus visit reservations at least one week prior to your visit). Once you complete your registration form the Office of Admissions will contact you to confirm the details of your visit. Then, all you need to do is come and experience CU!
